				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">This article is about large-scale production.  For the Iggy Pop piece, see <a href="The_Idiot_(album)" title="The Idiot (album)">The Idiot (album)</a>.  For the American funk band, see <a href="Mass_Production_(band)" title="Mass Production (band)">Mass Production (band)</a>.  For creation of matter, see <a href="Mass_generation" title="Mass generation">mass generation</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:277px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg/275px-Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg" width="275" height="191" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg/413px-Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg/550px-Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Consolidated_TB-32_production_line.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
